The draws for the Carabao Cup quarter-final will be conducted on Thursday night, with three places up for grabs. Manchester United, Tottenham Hotspur, Manchester City, Newcastle have all booked their places in the last eight. On Tuesday, Spurs saw off Chelsea via penalties. United hammered Brighton 3-0 and Newcastle also needed penalties to eliminate Newport. Holders Manchester City defeated Burnley 3-0 at Turf Moor, while Everton beat West Ham 4-1. The draw for the competition’s quarter-finals will take place after Liverpool’s match against Arsenal. Other ties scheduled for Thursday are Brentford vs Fulham and Aston Villa vs Stoke City. All four quarter-final matches will be played on December 22 and 23.